768. There ought to be a comma after indipisces. The active form of this verb occurs here and Asin. 11 2, 13, the deponent Prin. 224. Rud. v 2, 28. Epid. 111 4, 15: see Brix on Trin. 224. The Plautian MSS. give here inde poscere and Brix conjectures therefore that we should write isndepiscoe, which, he says, is defended by the analogy of depeciscor and defetiscor and attested by Festus.
